Z45A01 (FA CMA )  
T14:30170KeeleBC 214
Jonathan Silveira Students enrolling in PANF 3853 require a basic understanding of the 3D modeling and animation workflow, for example navigation within 3D spaces, importing objects, and basic terminology (e.g., mesh, material). The main software we will be using is Unreal Engine, but skills in other 3D modeling software will also be beneficial. Experience in rigging and animation would be excellent; however, the course will cover the basics in Blender. The course involves extensive use of motion capture suits, so it is important that students are comfortable wearing them. If you meet this criteria, please complete the permission form.

Z45A01 (FA CMA )  
T14:30170KeeleBC 214
Jonathan Silveira Students enrolling in PANF 3853 require a basic understanding of the 3D modeling and animation workflow, for example navigation within 3D spaces, importing objects, and basic terminology (e.g., mesh, material). The main software we will be using is Unreal Engine, but skills in other 3D modeling software will also be beneficial. Experience in rigging and animation would be excellent; however, the course will cover the basics in Blender. The course involves extensive use of motion capture suits, so it is important that students are comfortable wearing them. If you meet this criteria, please complete the permission form.
